In this statement, President Obama discusses the state of the U.S. economy. He highlights the fact that America's businesses created another 158,000 jobs in the previous month, and that the unemployment rate has fallen to 4.9%. He also mentions that over the past six years, businesses have added 14 million new jobs, and that wages have grown at their fastest rate since the economic crisis. However, he acknowledges that there is still work to be done, particularly in addressing the challenges posed by the global economy and ensuring that economic progress is felt by all Americans. He also discusses his budget plans, which include investments in education, job training, clean energy, and infrastructure. The President emphasizes the need to continue on the current path of progress and address the concerns and anxieties of the American people.